        "body": "This PR adds the `--html-resources` CLI flag to control whether to use a bundled version of the CSS and (if added in the future) JS, or to rely on a CDN. When the flag is set to `bundled` (the default), the `BULMA_VERSION` env var will be ignored, while if it's set to `cdn` the old behavior is restored.\r\n\r\nNotable things to keep in mind while reviewing this PR:\r\n\r\n* https://github.com/mozilla/grcov/pull/1086 already attempted this, but didn't followup on review feedback.\r\n\r\n* The bundled Bulma code was taken from the `bulma/css/bulma.min.css` file in the [archive on GitHub releases](https://github.com/jgthms/bulma/releases/download/0.9.1/bulma-0.9.1.zip).\r\n \r\n* ~~Even though I'd *love* to have this as the default, technically it's a breaking change. So the default behavior is now `--html-resources=cdn` rather than `--html-resources=bundled`. Let me know if I should make the bundled behavior the default.~~ It's now the default.\r\n\r\n* Bundling Bulma in grcov means we need to comply with Bulma's license while redistributing grcov. I added the MIT license file in the `src/bulma` directory, ~~and changed Cargo's license field to `MPL-2.0 AND MIT`~~.\r\n\r\nFixes https://github.com/mozilla/grcov/issues/1079",
